No problem migrating to the compact form, if that is the project standard; however, in the context of argument checking, I personally find the extended form more explicit and more consistent when accompanied by other checks as in:
if (iri == null) {
	throw new NullPointerException("null iri");
}

if (iri.indexOf(':') < 0) {
	throw new IllegalArgumentException("missing colon in absolute IRI");
}

